\title{croquis: Transit Sketch Planning with GTFS}
\description{
Tools for rapidly creating detailed and realistic transit networks and schedules in GTFS format, including a front-end Shiny app called Croquis. Introduces the Simplified Speed and Frequency Structure (ssfs), a data structure that simplifies GTFS creation and editing. Includes functions for conversion between SSFS and GTFS formats. Includes a calibration engine which adjusts SSFS speeds based on a reference GTFS. Output GTFS are compatible with travel demand and accessibility analysis tools such as r5r.
